Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Frontend Software Engineer* role with *BambooHR*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production-grade web applications, AI-powered features, and REST API integrations, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered frontend and full-stack systems that directly reflect the React depth, AI integration enthusiasm, and collaborative engineering this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built generative code solutions for JavaScript/TypeScript developers — crafting API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows that streamline REST API integration across 1,000+ platform endpoints. I integrated AI-powered features using prompt engineering, dynamic content rendering, and natural-language-to-action translation via an MCP interaction layer backed by Claude and Codex — directly mirroring BambooHR's own use of AI tools like Windsurf, ChatGPT, and Claude in daily development. REST API routing and concurrency optimizations I drove cut end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I led React-based development of an Identity & Access Management platform — building complex web UI components and pages with HTML/CSS and JavaScript for thousands of users across 30+ enterprise SaaS applications. I also built an AI-powered support chatbot integrating dynamic content rendering and natural-language querying into the UI, reducing ticket resolution time by 20%. Together, these roles have prepared me to collaborate closely with UX designers, contribute to the Bamboo product's ongoing improvement, and make it count from day one.

My academic background reinforces the collaborative, growth-oriented culture BambooHR values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I led hands-on workshops on building AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students — breaking down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly. This experience reflects BambooHR's values of growing from good to great and leading from where you are, and shapes the way I communicate across engineering, design, and product teams.

I have always been passionate about building software that sets people free to do great work, and I am excited about BambooHR's mission to transform HR through a people intelligence platform that makes work better for everyone. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

